THE SITE IS LOCATED AT THE NATIONAL PARK SERVICE TEST WELL INSIDE RUSSELL CAVE NATIONAL MONUMENT BOUNDARIES. THE WELL WAS DRILLED JUST NORTH OF RUSSELL CAVE IN 1962 AS PART OF A STUDY TO LOCATE GROUND WATER SOURCES ADEQUATE FOR THE NEEDS OF PROPOSED PARK DEVELOPMENT.  THE SITE FOR DRILLING THE WELL WAS SELECTED BASED ON CONVENIENCE TO PARK PLANNING AND THE LOCATION OF KNOWN CAVES WHICH WERE A SOURCE OF SURFACE POLLUTION.
